## Connecting This Back to OpenMRS

OpenMRS is used in real clinical settings — including hospitals and clinics in some of the most under-resourced healthcare environments in the world. That context matters for how I think about this project.

A GRC failure in an OpenMRS deployment is not just a compliance problem. If patient records become inaccessible because of a ransomware attack, or if records are tampered with because of weak access controls, or if the system goes down because backups were never tested — those failures affect real patients and real clinicians trying to deliver care.

That framing changes how I want to approach the rest of this challenge. I am not building a compliance portfolio. I am working through what it would actually take to secure a system that people depend on. That feels like the right way to think about it.

